<p align="center"><font size="6" color="#000080">SCORM Background (2)</font></p>

<p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080"><b>Problem:</b><br>
Many of the first web-based "Learning Management System" (LMS) products used proprietary "middle ware" and data models to track learner performance.&nbsp;</font></p>
<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Learning content couldn't be moved from one LMS environment to
    another</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">LMS products often couldn't integrate learning content created for other
    systems</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Couldn't create searchable content or content repositories</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
<!--msthemelist--></table><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
<p align="center"><img border="1" src="images/Web_HTML_DB.jpg" width="387" height="284"></p>
<p align="left"><font size="4" color="#000080"><br>
</font></p>
<p align="left"><font size="4" color="#000080"><b>New Vision:<br>
</b><br>
The ADL team envisioned a new approach for Internet delivered learning:</font></p>
<!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Learning objects can be
    reusable, searchable, durable, and accessible</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Customized learning experiences that match a learner's
    needs, assembled &quot;on the fly&quot;&nbsp;</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Learning
    experiences adapt intelligently to the learner</font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
  <!--msthemelist--><tr><td valign="baseline" width="42"><img src="_themes/blocks/blobul1e.gif" width="15" height="15" hspace="13"></td><td valign="top" width="100%"><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
    <p align="left" style="line-height: 150%"><font size="4" color="#000080">Learning objects could include assessments, simulations, performance support,
    and directed learning experiences<br>
    </font><!--mstheme--></font><!--msthemelist--></td></tr>
<!--msthemelist--></table><!--mstheme--><font face="Arial, Arial, Helvetica">
